      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "INGA RYDER (4) hit the ground running with a slick early sectional but had to settle for a minor placing when a 6 length third over 390m at this track, clocking 22.66. Expected to feature in the finish again. MOONLIGHT HAZE (7) still a maiden but rarely out of the finish recording six placings from eight starts. Hasn't been able to break through recently but continues to race well, filling the minors at the last two starts. Racing well and deserves a win. RIGHT PATH (8) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at Healesville over 300m behind Crackerjack Greg (17.66) in a Maiden. Placed at his previous run. Comes out of a hot form race last start. Shapes as one to consider. PAW PEARL (2) cannot be written off despite a miss here at her latest outing.",
